newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline falls $2 despite support, $18 Nov-Dec.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline falls $2 despite support, $18 Nov-Dec.

text.p: NWE gasoline slipped $2.00 a tonne on Wednesday as weak crude and U.S. gasoline weighed on the European market.

Eurograde barges slipped to about $235.50 for October loadings by the close after a trade earlier at $236.00 and $237.00 for a top-up. A barge for loading 1-15 November traded at $234.00, compared to November swaps at $228.50.
Demand for regular barges remains good around $229.00 and Polish demand also underpinned prices.
